(b) Material specification format (AMS, MIL-SPEC, SAE, ASTM, EN, DIN, etc.)
(c) Part number format
(d) Quality / certification notes (IATF, PPAP, AS9100, NADCAP, FAA, etc.)
(e) Industry indicators — automotive OEM, aerospace, general mechanical, oil & gas, medical, etc.

Classify the domain into one of:
- "Automotive": IATF 16949, PPAP/APQP, OEM standards (GMW3059, Ford GSDS), SAE material grades
- "Aerospace": MIL-STD-100, ASME Y14.100, AMS material specs, AS9100/NADCAP, cage code P/N format
- "General Mechanical": ISO 2768, DIN, BS, EN standards — standard industrial machined parts
- "Other": electrical schematics, P&IDs, civil/structural, sheet metal layout, anything non-machined

Set in_scope to true for Automotive, Aerospace, and General Mechanical (any machined part drawing).
Set in_scope to false only for drawings that are clearly not machined parts (schematics, structural, sheet metal, etc.).
Provide 3-5 evidence bullets.
